description:
Write a program to check the priority of the four operators: addition (+), subtraction (-), multiplication (*), and division (/). You need to determine which operators have higher precedence over others.

#### `Input Format:`
`The input consists of the four operators separated by spaces: + - * / or No any input It should simply print the predefined message (i.e. Sample output) without processing any input`

#### `Output Format:`
`The program outputs the priority of the operators based on their precedence. You should indicate which operators have higher precedence over others.`

#### `Sample Input:`
```
+ - * /   Or  No any input
```

#### `Sample Output:`
```
Multiplication (*) and Division (/) have higher precedence than Addition (+) and Subtraction (-).
```

#### `Constraints:`
- ***`The program should simply print the predefined message (i.e. Sample output) without processing any input.`***
title: Operator Precedence/Priority Check

default_testcase.expected_output: Multiplication (*) and Division (/) have higher precedence than Addition (+) and Subtraction (-).
